const summary = "'`Dataset ds001_aml contained ${r.n} patients and ${r.outcomeSum} objective responses (${pp(r.outcomeMean)}%). Effect estimates below are signed absolute changes in objective_response probability; positive values mean higher response. I used risk-difference z tests for binary/subgroup comparisons, univariate linear probability regressions for continuous features, and HC1-robust adjusted linear probability models for adjusted main effects and interactions.'"\\n\\nMain treatment and biomarker findings:\\n- treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine showed the clearest treatment association: unadjusted response "'${pp(treatment('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').p1)}% vs "'${pp(treatment('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').p0)}%, risk difference "'${pp(treatment('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').effect)} percentage points (p="'${pstr(treatment('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').p)}); adjusted coefficient "'${pp(adjT('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').beta)} percentage points (p="'${pstr(adjT('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine').p)}).\\n- treatment_7plus3 was not associated with materially higher response overall: risk difference "'${pp(treatment('"'treatment_7plus3').effect)} percentage points (p="'${pstr(treatment('"'treatment_7plus3').p)}).\\n- npm1_mutation was strongly favorable after adjustment, with a "'${pp(adjB('"'npm1_mutation').beta)} percentage-point higher response probability (p="'${pstr(adjB('"'npm1_mutation').p)}).\\n- tp53_mutation and complex_karyotype were adverse: adjusted coefficients "'${pp(adjB('"'tp53_mutation').beta)} and "'${pp(adjB('"'complex_karyotype').beta)} percentage points, respectively (p="'${pstr(adjB('"'tp53_mutation').p)} and p="'${pstr(adjB('"'complex_karyotype').p)}).\\n\\nClinical burden and inflammatory/proliferative patterns:\\n- Higher weight_loss_pct_6mo, blast_pct_marrow, wbc_k_per_ul, and crp_mg_l were each associated with lower response; higher albumin_g_dl was associated with higher response. The largest continuous effect was weight loss: "'${pp(cont('"'weight_loss_pct_6mo').effect)} percentage points per 5 percentage-point increase (p="'${pstr(cont('"'weight_loss_pct_6mo').p)}).\\n- A combined low-albumin/high-CRP subgroup had lower response ("'${pp(r.inflamedEffect.effect)} percentage points, p=${pstr(r.inflamedEffect.p)}). A high-WBC/high-LDH subgroup also had lower response (${pp(r.proliferativeEffect.effect)} percentage points, p=${pstr(r.proliferativeEffect.p)}).'"\\n\\nSubgroup heterogeneity and interactions:\\n- The venetoclax/azacitidine association was concentrated in patients unfit for intensive therapy: within unfit patients, response was "'${pp(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_pos.p1)}% with treatment vs ${pp(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_pos.p0)}% without treatment (risk difference ${pp(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_pos.effect)} points, p=${pstr(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_pos.p)}). In fit patients, the difference was ${pp(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_neg.effect)} points and was not significant at 0.05 (p=${pstr(r.subgroups.ven_unfit_neg.p)}). The adjusted interaction term was strongly positive (${pp(intx('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine','unfit_for_intensive').beta)} points, p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine','unfit_for_intensive').p)}).\\n- tp53_mutation attenuated the venetoclax/azacitidine association: adjusted interaction "'${pp(intx('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine','tp53_mutation').beta)} points (p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine','tp53_mutation').p)}).\\n- complex_karyotype reduced the treatment_7plus3 association: adjusted interaction "'${pp(intx('"'treatment_7plus3','complex_karyotype').beta)} points (p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_7plus3','complex_karyotype').p)}).\\n\\nTargeted treatment-biomarker hypotheses were mostly not supported. Midostaurin by flt3_itd ("'${pp(intx('"'treatment_midostaurin','flt3_itd').beta)} points, p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_midostaurin','flt3_itd').p)}), gilteritinib by flt3_itd ("'${pp(intx('"'treatment_gilteritinib','flt3_itd').beta)} points, p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_gilteritinib','flt3_itd').p)}), and enasidenib by idh2_mutation ("'${pp(intx('"'treatment_enasidenib','idh2_mutation').beta)} points, p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_enasidenib','idh2_mutation').p)}) were null. The ivosidenib by idh1_mutation interaction was significant but negative ("'${pp(intx('"'treatment_ivosidenib','idh1_mutation').beta)} points, p="'${pstr(intx('"'treatment_ivosidenib','idh1_mutation').p)}), opposite the hypothesized direction. Age did not materially modify venetoclax/azacitidine or 7+3 associations.\\n\\nOverall conclusion: in this cohort, objective_response was most strongly patterned by venetoclax/azacitidine use in unfit patients, favorable npm1_mutation status, adverse tp53_mutation/complex_karyotype status, and systemic disease-burden markers. Several familiar targeted therapy-biomarker pairings did not show positive response heterogeneity in these data, while TP53 and complex karyotype appeared to blunt treatment-associated response."'`;
fs.writeFileSync('"'analysis_summary.txt', summary);
